## Notes

- **NULL values** indicate missing data requiring further research
- **Modded = 0**: Historical data (original equipment)
- **Modded = 1**: Modified/fictional variants
- **Length format**: /## represents caliber length (e.g., /50 = 50 calibers)
- **Armor values**: All measurements in inches (Class A for face/sides, Class B for roof)
- **Performance rates**: Degrees per second for traverse/elevation
